# TypeScript (.ts) — condensed

Aligned with `.claude/rules/typescript-conventions.md`, **workspace-packages.mdc**, and coding-standards.

- Keep **cyclomatic complexity ≤ 6** for all non-TSX TypeScript; fail fast at module boundaries where appropriate.
- **Data layer:** `@minute-menus/supabase-service` and persistence packages; inject Supabase client; no service role in browser.
- **API routes:** admin client server-only; use `@minute-menus/logger`, `mailer`, `api-helpers`, `payments`; validate inputs.
- **Packages:** shared logic in `packages/*`; types from `@minute-menus/types`; errors from `@minute-menus/errors`.
- **lib / scripts:** shims and tooling only where documented; scripts assume secrets stay off the client bundle.

Product-specific constraints stay in CLAUDE.md / agents.md.
